Raphael.

You know me too well.
Fear sits in the soul of all - to tame it, we must name it. Astarion - what is his deepest fear?
If I admired nobody I would travel alone. You have earned my admiration. And more.
I'm not opposed to a bowl of something mysterious and rib-sticking, but I certainly don't identify as one.
Honestly - probably. But hopefully not any time soon. I've got a lot of living to do yet.
Hearing it said out loud - yes, I fear it is true. Fate seems determined to make a sacrifice of me.
None. Her name will be lost to time.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
Darkness as the dryad's vision ends. When the player opens their eyes, it is Orin stood before them. She smiles wickedly.

Extreme close-up on the eyes of player to help with the transition
EditorData.SFXTags: [AK] SFX player returns back to reality
EditorData.VFXTags: [AK] VFX player returns back to reality

Text.Value: You return, stira - good. Violence is like fire - it burns all those in its path. I feared you caught in the flames.
I would never!
I care only for myself.
This city of stone and steel is an endless scream in nature's womb. I have felt no peace here. Until now.
The day he made his pact.
Public adoration.
There is a hollowness between you, a void that your futures may come to fill with darkness.
Many things delight the heart, but only one makes it sing. Tell me, what is her idea of a perfect day?
A perfect score - I'm flattered. Have you been studying up on me every night at camp?
Oh you're very sweet. I wouldn't say no to some gory vengeance personally, but that was an adorable answer.
A fateful night. I'm not apt to forget it - or who spent it with me.
You flatter me... but also overestimate our bond, I think. Perhaps there is another you can turn to.
Good company and an even better vintage.
A perfect score. It seems you know me better than I know myself.
Like I need a dryad to tell me what I feel.
Joining up with me.
A fair assumption. Perhaps not the truest answer of all, but still in good judgement.
You did pretty well there, soldier. I have to say, I'm impressed.
I await with a heart full and happy - eager to begin.

You return, stira. I pray the hearts of you and your companion are ready - for love is a fragile blossom, and we will test its resilience. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
No. And if you refer to me as 'my dear' again, I will cut out your tongue.
Turn her back on Lolth.
Our touch has been that of sunlight. But now we must look beyond - to the uncertain. To the future.
Just the sound of his name makes my blood boil - probably literally. Can't stand the fucker. Ding ding.
Independence.
Indeed. You were a source of light among shadows. Still are, for that matter.
Quite right. This is my fate, wrought by loyalty, entrusted to Vlaakith.
No thank you. Sounds as appealing as milking cottage cheese directly from a geriatric cow.
Gale: the learned wizard. The charming gentleman. The walking apocalypse.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player takes a second step, moving even closer to the center for the trunk to the companion.

Text.Value: At dusk. The light favours his complexion.
Listen. Think. When is he most comfortable?
A source of pride, true. I can think of greater feats, but that one is cherished all the same.
I see you. I see the bond between you. So tender. So fragile. But do you see it for yourselves?

Synopsis: The dryad from the circus of the last days is mastering a "Test your love" game, where player can ask a companion to participate and answer some questions about them for the approval rating.
